
<html>
<body style="background-color:#FFFFFF">
<center>
    <div id="page-content-wrapper">
      <div class="page-content">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-12">
              <h1>
                <%= link_to image_tag("parkr.png", :width => "20%", :height => "20%"), parking_meters_path, {class: "logo"} %>
              </h1>
              <h3>
              <%=link_to "Home", parking_meters_path%>
              </h3>
              <h2>
                Parkr is..
              </h2>
              <p>
                ..an online parking planner for the city of Vancouver, here to help you plan ahead. You can search for parking meters within
                a given radius around your intended location, and view information that matters to you, like rates, time limits,
                and times in-effect. Additionally, you can see all locations of auto-related crime that has occurred over the most
                current year, so that you can avoid areas known for break-ins and feel more at ease.
              </p>
              <h2>
                We are..
              </h2>
              <p>
                ..a team of 3 UBC Undergrads studying Computer Science who created this website as a project for our CPSC 310
                class. The assignment was to create a web app that pulled and utilized information from a local database.
                For Parkr, we used parking meter, auto-related crime, and electric vehicle charging stations data from the
                City Of Vancouver.
              </p>
              <h3>
                Database Credits
              </h3>
